// src/pages/brands/maytag.astro
// Tier 3 brand hub, Maytag (~265 GSC imp/3mo across 26 queries; "maytag repair near me"
// 61 imp pos 18 leads, several queries top-1 to top-3 already ranking).
// Built from SERP research 2026-04-30. Tone reference: frigidaire.astro (similar volume tier),
// whirlpool.astro (parent-corp consistency). Voice discipline: Whirlpool ownership context
// (2006 acquisition, shared parts platform), "built to last" reputation honestly framed,
// Bravos / Maxima / Centennial line distinction, F-code parity with Whirlpool. Streamlined
// 9-section hub for Tier 3 efficiency. NO fabricated client names.

import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import ServiceHero from '../../components/ServiceHero.astro';
import { MAIN_PHONE } from '../../data/branches';

const phone = MAIN_PHONE;
const phoneRaw = MAIN_PHONE.replace(/\D/g, '');
const phoneHref = `tel:+1${phoneRaw}`;
const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/maytag/";

const title = "Maytag Appliance Repair, Same-Day Service Across Southern California";
const description = "Maytag appliance repair across LA, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino & Riverside counties. Whirlpool platform, OEM parts, $89 dx. BHGS #A49573, EPA 608.";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "Is Maytag still its own company?",
    a: "Maytag is owned by Whirlpool Corporation, which acquired the brand in 2006 for $1.7 billion. Operationally, Maytag continues to be marketed and sold as a distinct brand with its own \"built to last\" positioning, but engineering, parts, and supply chain run through Whirlpool's manufacturing infrastructure (the same Ohio, Tennessee, and Iowa plants that build Whirlpool-branded appliances). From a homeowner's standpoint, this is good news for service: Maytag and Whirlpool washers and dryers are mechanically identical or near-identical across most model generations, with cosmetic trim and badging differences, which means parts availability is excellent and our techs cross-reference between the two brands constantly. Most Maytag service calls run faster than equivalent calls on standalone brands because we already know the platform."
  },
  {
    q: "Are Maytag washers and dryers really \"built to last\"?",
    a: "Honest answer. Maytag's marketing positioning around durability is partially true, the heavier-duty Maytag Commercial-Technology models (MVWP washers, MEDP dryers) actually do use commercial-grade components and run longer than their entry-tier Whirlpool counterparts. The Bravos top-load and Maxima front-load consumer lines are more typical mid-tier appliances, reliable, but not standout, and very similar to Whirlpool Cabrio and Duet equivalents because they share the platform. Across all Maytag laundry, the \"built to last\" claim is closer to true on the higher-spec models and closer to ordinary on the entry-tier. Our techs see Maytag laundry every week, the Commercial-Technology models do hold up notably better than average through year 12-15 with normal maintenance."
  },
  {
    q: "What's the difference between Bravos, Maxima, and Centennial?",
    a: "Three Maytag laundry families. Bravos is the top-load HE family, most are impeller-driven, no agitator, electronic controls. MVWB-series model numbers. Service tree mirrors Whirlpool Cabrio: lid lock (year 3-6), drain pump (year 6-9), suspension rod kit (year 9+), main control board. Maxima is the front-load family, MHW-series. Service tree mirrors Whirlpool Duet: drain pump (year 5-8), door boot (year 8-10), bearing service (year 8-12, $585-$880 with seal). Centennial is the entry-tier top-load and dryer line, simpler, more mechanical-feeling, drive-belt transmission on the washers. Centennial is the most reliable of the three through year 10+ because it has fewer electronic components to fail. All three families share parts with their Whirlpool equivalents through Whirlpool Corp's distribution network."
  },
  {
    q: "What's an F01 / F02 / F11 / F26 error code on my Maytag washer?",
    a: "Same codes as Whirlpool washers because Maytag and Whirlpool share the platform. F01, main control board (CCU) communication or internal fault. Reset by unplugging for 10 minutes; if F01 returns, CCU replacement ($345-$525). F02, long drain error; pump, hose, or filter clog ($145-$385). F11, serial communication error between CCU and MCU; one of the boards or the harness between them ($345-$680). F26, door / lid switch error; lid lock on Bravos or door lock on Maxima ($145-$215 typical). About 70% of F26 codes resolve at lid/door lock replacement."
  },
  {
    q: "How much does Maytag appliance repair cost in LA?",
    a: "Diagnostic is $89, applied toward the repair when work is approved. Maytag pricing matches Whirlpool because of the shared platform: refrigerator door gasket $180-$280; refrigerator water inlet valve $185-$285; refrigerator ice maker assembly $245-$385; washer lid switch / lid lock (Bravos top-load) $145-$215; washer drain pump $245-$385; washer door boot (Maxima front-load) $285-$425; washer main control board (CCU) $345-$525; dryer thermal fuse + vent inspection $145-$245; dryer heating element $285-$425; dryer drum belt + idler $195-$295; dishwasher drain pump $245-$385; range surface igniter $145-$215; oven bake element $185-$285. Front-load Maxima bearing + drum seal as a set $585-$880. Commercial-Technology premium uplift on heavier-duty models: 10-15% above standard Maytag pricing."
  },
  {
    q: "Do you service Maytag in Sherman Oaks, Westwood, Irvine, and other parts of SoCal?",
    a: "Yes, Maytag has solid distribution across our 5-county service area, with concentrations in production-builder homes throughout the Inland Empire (Rancho Cucamonga, Fontana, Ontario), Sherman Oaks and the broader San Fernando Valley, plus Westwood and the older Westside neighborhoods where Maytag's reliability reputation has driven buying decisions. Pasadena and Glendale see strong Maxima front-load installations in renovation kitchens. Orange County (Newport Beach, Irvine, Costa Mesa, Tustin) tracks similar mixed patterns. The 8-branch dispatch grid in the hero CTA shows the closest dispatch territory for any address, same parts on truck as Whirlpool, same diagnostic procedures. Our techs treat Maytag and Whirlpool as a single platform when planning truck stock."
  }
];

const schemaJsons = [
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Service",
    "@id": canonical + "#service",
    "serviceType": "Maytag Appliance Repair",
    "name": "Maytag Appliance Repair, Same Day Appliance Repair",
    "url": canonical,
    "description": "Same-day Maytag appliance repair across Los Angeles, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, and Riverside counties. Refrigerators (MFI French Door, MFF Side-by-Side, MBR top-freezer), washers (Bravos top-load, Maxima front-load, Centennial entry-tier), dryers (MED electric, MGD gas, Centennial), ranges, dishwashers, microwaves. Factory-trained on shared Whirlpool platform, Maytag and Whirlpool engineering identical or near-identical across most model generations. $89 residential diagnostic, applied toward repair.",
