---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical}>

<Fragment slot="head-scripts">
  {schemaJsons.map((schema) => (<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />))}
</Fragment>

<ServiceHero
  eyebrow="LA · Orange · Ventura · San Bernardino · Riverside Counties"
  title="Maytag Appliance Repair, Across Southern California"
  subtitle="Refrigerator (MFI / MFF / MBR) · Bravos top-load + Maxima front-load · Centennial · MED / MGD dryers · Range · Dishwasher · Microwave. Whirlpool-platform parts on every truck. Factory-trained, OEM parts. $89 diagnostic, same day across five SoCal counties."
  heroImageTitle="Maytag Appliance Repair"
  showBranches={true}
/>

<!-- 01 INTRO -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">01, About this service</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Maytag, Whirlpool-owned since 2006, distinct brand voice, same parts network.</h2>

    <p>Maytag is owned by Whirlpool Corporation (acquired 2006 for $1.7 billion). The brand continues with its own "built to last" marketing positioning, but engineering, manufacturing, and parts supply run through Whirlpool's infrastructure, the same Ohio, Tennessee, and Iowa plants that build Whirlpool-branded products. For service, this is excellent news: Maytag and Whirlpool washers, dryers, and refrigerators are mechanically identical or near-identical across most model generations, with cosmetic trim and badging differences. Our trucks carry parts that fit both brands, our techs cross-reference diagnostic procedures constantly, and most Maytag service calls run faster than equivalent calls on standalone brands because we already know the platform.</p>

    <p>Two Maytag-specific service realities shape every diagnostic call. First, the <strong>"built to last" reputation is partially true</strong>: the Commercial-Technology models (MVWP washers, MEDP dryers) actually do use heavier-duty components and outlast equivalent Whirlpool-branded entry-tier units; the standard Bravos / Maxima / Centennial consumer models are typical mid-tier appliances that mirror their Whirlpool Cabrio / Duet counterparts. We tell customers honestly which tier they have. Second, <strong>F-code error diagnostics on Maytag washers and dryers are identical to Whirlpool</strong>, F01, F02, F11, F26, and the rest follow the same diagnostic tree. A tech who knows Whirlpool washer codes already knows Maytag.</p>

    <p>This page covers Maytag repair across all major appliance categories. Every service call gets a $89 residential diagnostic (applied toward the repair when work is approved), OEM parts where we can, and an honest written quote before any work begins.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 02 REFRIGERATOR -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">02, Maytag refrigerator repair</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Maytag refrigerators, solid mid-tier, shared Whirlpool platform.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Maytag refrigerators come in three main families: MFI French Door (MFI2570FEZ, MFI2269FRZ), MFF Side-by-Side (MFF2055FRZ, MFF2258FEZ), and MBR top/bottom freezer (MBR2258FEZ, MBR1957FEZ). All share Whirlpool refrigeration architecture with cosmetic trim differences. Service tree is conventional and consistent.</p>

    <p>Most-common service items by year:</p>

    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li><strong>Year 4-7, Ice maker assembly:</strong> Modular ice makers shared with Whirlpool platform. Replacement $245-$385.</li>
      <li><strong>Year 5-9, Water inlet valve:</strong> Dual-coil solenoid wear; partial fills, slow dispensing. Replacement $185-$285.</li>
      <li><strong>Year 6-10, Evaporator fan motor:</strong> Whirring or grinding sound; intermittent cooling. Replacement $245-$385.</li>
      <li><strong>Year 7-11, Defrost system:</strong> Heater, thermostat, or sensor failure. Diagnostic separates which item. $185-$345 replacement.</li>
      <li><strong>Year 8-12, Door gasket:</strong> Especially in coastal homes. Replacement $180-$280.</li>
      <li><strong>Year 8-12, Main control board:</strong> Especially after grid power surges. Replacement $345-$525.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>Note: Maytag (along with Whirlpool, KitchenAid, and JennAir) Side-by-Side and French Door refrigerators built between 2018 and 2021 are subject to a class action settlement covering a wire-harness defect that causes ice maker, dispenser, and control panel failures. Settlement claim deadline is November 2, 2026. We verify class-action eligibility on diagnostic visits, if your unit qualifies and the claim window is still open, the work routes through the settlement, not through paid repair.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 03 LAUNDRY -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">03, Maytag laundry repair</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Maytag washers and dryers, Bravos, Maxima, Centennial, MED / MGD.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Maytag laundry is the brand's strongest category, Bravos top-load (MVWB), Maxima front-load (MHW), Centennial entry-tier top-load and dryers, and Commercial-Technology premium models. All share Whirlpool engineering with platform-wide parts compatibility.</p>

    <p><strong>Bravos top-load (MVWB-series)</strong> mirrors Whirlpool Cabrio service tree exactly: lid lock / lid switch (year 3-6, $145-$215, F26 fix), drain pump (year 6-9, $245-$385), drive belt + shift actuator (year 5-8), suspension rod kit (year 9+ for unbalanced loads, $245-$385), main control board (year 8-12).</p>

    <p><strong>Maxima front-load (MHW-series)</strong> mirrors Whirlpool Duet: drain pump (year 5-8), door boot (year 8-10, $285-$425), bearing + drum seal as a set (year 8-12, $585-$880, replacing only bearing without seal fails again within months), main control board (CCU). F11 CCU↔MCU communication errors common after power surges.</p>

    <p><strong>Centennial</strong> is the entry-tier top-load washer and dryer line, simpler architecture, more mechanical-feeling, drive-belt transmission on the washers. Centennial is actually the most reliable Maytag laundry through year 10+ because it has fewer electronic components. Service tree: lid switch, drive coupler, motor coupling, water inlet valve, drain pump.</p>

    <p><strong>MED electric and MGD gas dryers</strong> share platform with Whirlpool dryers. Standard service items: thermal fuse blown from vent blockage (always inspect the vent before replacing the fuse, fuse alone fails again within weeks), heating element burnout (year 8-12), drum belt + idler pulley wear (year 6-9), thermistor drift causing intermittent heating. Gas dryers add gas valve coil failure (year 9-12). F01 dryer error indicates main control board (CCU) internal short, usually power-surge damage.</p>

    <p><strong>Commercial-Technology models</strong> (MVWP and MEDP) use heavier-duty components and notably outlast their consumer-tier counterparts. We see fewer service calls on these and the calls we do run tend to be on year 12+ units rather than the year 5-9 window typical of consumer Bravos / Maxima.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 04 OTHER APPLIANCES -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">04, Other Maytag appliances</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Maytag dishwashers, ranges, microwaves.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Outside refrigeration and laundry, Maytag's appliance breadth is narrower than Whirlpool's but covers the major kitchen categories at competitive price points.</p>

    <div class="appliance-grid">
      <div class="appliance-card">
        <h3>Maytag Dishwashers (MDB / MDT)</h3>
        <p>MDB-series base and MDT-series premium dishwashers share Whirlpool platform. Common service: drain pump, water inlet valve, control board, door latch (year 6-9), heating element/thermistor. Maytag dishwashers in the value tier track similar reliability to Whirlpool WDF-series.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="appliance-card">
        <h3>Maytag Ranges (MGR gas, MER electric)</h3>
        <p>MGR gas and MER electric freestanding ranges. Common service: surface igniter (gas), bake/broil element (electric), oven temperature sensor, control board. F1, F3, F4 codes follow Whirlpool diagnostic tree.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="appliance-card">
        <h3>Maytag Microwaves (MMV over-the-range)</h3>
        <p>MMV over-the-range microwaves. Common service: door switch (3-switch system; one fails, microwave won't start), magnetron, turntable motor, charcoal/grease filters. Less prominent in Maytag's lineup than washer / dryer / refrigeration.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="appliance-card">
        <h3>Maytag Wall Ovens &amp; Cooktops</h3>
        <p>Smaller part of Maytag's catalog. MEW wall ovens and MEC cooktops follow standard Whirlpool platform service procedures. Hinge + spring service common at year 7-10 on heavy oven doors.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="appliance-card">
        <h3>Maytag Commercial Laundry</h3>
        <p>Commercial Maytag washers and dryers (MFR, MDG models) for laundromats, multi-family housing, and on-premise laundry. Different service tree, coin / card systems, heavier-duty motors, longer-cycle programming. Specialty work; we dispatch commercial-trained techs.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="appliance-card">
        <h3>Whirlpool family cross-coverage</h3>
        <p>Our trucks carry parts that fit Maytag, Whirlpool, KitchenAid, and Amana on the same platform. Cross-reference diagnostic procedures; same parts network through Whirlpool Corp distribution. This is one of the rare advantages of brand consolidation under one parent, service depth scales across the family.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 05 MODELS -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">05, Maytag models we service most often</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Bravos, Maxima, Centennial, MED / MGD families.</h2>

    <p class="lead">A representative sample of Maytag model families our techs service routinely. Maytag's catalog is narrower than Whirlpool's but the model families below cover most of what shows up on our route.</p>

    <div class="model-grid">
      <div class="model-card">
        <h3>Refrigerators</h3>
        <p class="model-list">MFI2570FEZ · MFI2269FRZ · MFF2055FRZ · MFF2258FEZ · MBR2258FEZ · MBR1957FEZ</p>
        <p>MFI French Door, MFF Side-by-Side, MBR top / bottom freezer. 2018-2021 manufacture window covered by wire-harness class action.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="model-card">
        <h3>Bravos Top-Load Washers</h3>
        <p class="model-list">MVWB835DW · MVWX655DW · MVWB755DW · MVWB965HC · MVWB825JW</p>
        <p>Bravos HE top-load family. MVWB-series. Lid lock and suspension rod dominate service mix.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="model-card">
        <h3>Maxima Front-Load Washers</h3>
        <p class="model-list">MHW8630HW · MHW6630HW · MHW5630HW · MHW8200FC · MHW3505FW</p>
        <p>Maxima front-load family. MHW-series. Drain pump, door boot, bearing service. Year 8-12 bearing typical.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="model-card">
        <h3>Centennial Top-Load + Dryers</h3>
        <p class="model-list">MVWC465HW · MVWC565FW · MEDC465HW · MEDC555DW · MGDC465HW</p>
        <p>Entry-tier Centennial. Simpler architecture, more mechanical-feeling. Most reliable Maytag laundry through year 10+.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="model-card">
        <h3>MED Electric + MGD Gas Dryers</h3>
        <p class="model-list">MED5500FC · MED7000DW · MGDB955FW · MGD5500FC · MED6230HW</p>
        <p>Standard MED electric, MGD gas. Same service tree as Whirlpool WED / WGD. Thermal fuse + vent + element.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="model-card">
        <h3>Commercial-Technology Premium</h3>
        <p class="model-list">MVWP575GW · MVWP576KW · MEDP575GW · MGDP575GW</p>
        <p>Heavier-duty consumer-marketed models. MVWP washers, MEDP / MGDP dryers. Longer service life than standard Bravos / Maxima, year 12-15 typical with normal maintenance.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 06 PRICING -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">06, Pricing</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">What Maytag appliance repair costs in Southern California.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Diagnostic is $89, applied toward the repair. Maytag pricing matches Whirlpool because of the shared platform. Labor and parts quoted in writing before any work begins.</p>

    <div class="pricing-grid">
      <div class="price-card">
        <div class="price-label">Diagnostic</div>
        <div class="price-amount">$89</div>
        <div class="price-desc">Waived when you approve repair</div>
      </div>
      <div class="price-card">
        <div class="price-label">Standard band</div>
        <div class="price-amount">$145–$385</div>
        <div class="price-desc">Lid lock · igniter · valve · drain pump · sensor · ice maker</div>
      </div>
      <div class="price-card">
        <div class="price-label">Major component</div>
        <div class="price-amount">$285–$525</div>
        <div class="price-desc">Control board · CCU · heating element · door boot</div>
      </div>
      <div class="price-card">
        <div class="price-label">Bearing / sealed-system</div>
        <div class="price-amount">$585–$880</div>
        <div class="price-desc">Maxima bearing + seal · refrigerant work</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="price-note">Wire-harness class action repairs on 2018-2021 refrigerators (Maytag / Whirlpool / KitchenAid / JennAir) route through the settlement claim process when the unit qualifies, not a paid repair through us. Commercial-Technology premium uplift: 10-15% above standard band on heavier-duty parts. Maytag commercial laundry (MFR coin-op, multi-family) is priced separately under our commercial service rates.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 07 RECENT REPAIRS -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">07, Recent repairs</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Maytag jobs from across the territory.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Two representative service calls, model, symptom, diagnosis, repair, and cost. Names and addresses omitted; the technical scenarios are typical of what we see on Maytag service.</p>

    <div class="repair-grid">
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>Maytag MVWB835DW Bravos top-load, Sherman Oaks</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> Washer fills and agitates normally but stalls before spin. F26 error code displayed mid-cycle.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Lid lock / lid switch assembly failure, most common Bravos service call (year 4-6 typical, mirrors Whirlpool Cabrio pattern). Switch ohms-out reading inconsistent on bench test, contact intermittent. Drive system tested fine; drain pump tested fine.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Lid lock / lid switch assembly replacement with OEM Whirlpool-platform part (in stock on the truck, same part fits Maytag and Whirlpool Cabrio). Verified normal lid-lock engagement and full cycle progression. F26 cleared.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost &amp; time:</strong> $185 total. Same-day, 50 minutes on-site.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>Maytag MED7000DW electric dryer, Westwood</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> Dryer running normal cycles but clothes coming out damp. Owner had run the same load through twice and still ended up partially wet.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Heating element ohms-out tested 14% above spec, early-stage burnout. Vent inspection: substantial lint accumulation throughout the duct run from dryer to exterior wall cap (typical of 2+ years without vent cleaning). Thermal fuse tested fine but element was clearly the primary issue, with vent restriction accelerating element wear.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Heating element replacement with OEM Whirlpool-platform part (in stock). Full vent run cleaning included as same-trip work. Verified normal exhaust airflow and complete drying on test cycle.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost &amp; time:</strong> $385 total. Same-day, 95 minutes on-site.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 08 FAQ -->
